[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm looking at options for managing database connections, like using try-with-resources to close PreparedStatements properly. I wonder if issues arise from unclosed statements. To ensure clean database files during each run, maybe we can implement a unique in-memory option with @TempDir. Parameterized tests in JUnit 5 can take a temp directory as an argument. This could help avoid using stale data files from previous runs while ensuring functional coverage is maintained.
